<br>
Is anyone planning on posting that the idea of us 'experimenting' is ridiculous? They want us to fumble around wasting IP's all over the place at the cost of gimping ourselves? Thats way wrong and I want to tell them that.<br>
<br>
I also want to ask why, if we are intended to make use of blades, is EVERY melee weapon skill blue or dark blue to us.<br>
<br>
Lastly, perhaps they will give us an eta on the MA 'fixes' and these new weapons (he did mention new weapons in the interview right?). I'm gonna be so angry if I waste all my surplus points in 1he only to discover there's a brand new line of specialty MA weapons that are all piercing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=genjuro>Genjuro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#660000>(8/9/01 5:58:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is anyone planning on posting at the main site RE: weapo</span><hr size=1> I completely agree. One of the advantages listed in the guide books is &quot;Ma's have no need for weapons, but have a good bow skill&quot;<br>
<br>
Yet from the interview he hints that MA's can improve their preformance even further by experimenting with weapons. Bah! I experimented with a ritual dagger, 1he, requires 1 skill in 3 skills. <br>
<br>
I hit for 9 points of damage in between my punchs for 60. That's cool and all, but the best MA weapons require skills that aren't possible to reach without a profession specific line of buffs... which mind you we only have stuff that adds to MA in terms of attack rating. <br>
<br>
I'd hate to spend points for the nifty blades, if they implement more traditional MA weapons like nunchaku (enter the dragon anyone?)<br>
<br>
Tell us MA's that to do damage at higher levels we need weapons is like telling enforcers you need assualt rifles later on, and that soldiers need to go unarmed.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=81.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=81.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=81.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.threadControl?topicID=81.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=81.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=81.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub83.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thepunchingbag74708frm4">House Rules<option value="thepunchingbag74708frm1">Main Dojo